headline: CAG Q3 Deep Dive: Product Mix, Supply Chain Recovery, and Strategic Pricing Shape Results
summary: Packaged foods company Conagra Brands (NYSE:CAG) reported Q3 CY2025 results exceeding the market’s revenue expectations, but sales fell by 5.8% year on year to $2.63 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $0.39 per share was 17.4% above analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: Conagra Brands (CAG): Exploring Current Valuation After Recent Share Price Rebound
summary: Conagra Brands (CAG) has seen some turbulence lately, with its stock returning nearly 6% over the past week but down almost 31% year-to-date. Investors are trying to make sense of whether this recent pop could hint at a broader shift or is simply short-term volatility. See our latest analysis for Conagra Brands.
